1️⃣ What is JOIN?
Simple Idea

JOIN is used to combine data from multiple tables

👉 It answers:
“How do I connect data from different tables?”

Real-World Mental Model 🧠

Think:

You have 2 separate lists:

Students Table
id	name
1	Akshay
2	Rahul
Courses Table
student_id	course
1	CSE
2	ECE

👉 Now you want:

Akshay → CSE  
Rahul → ECE

To get this, you must JOIN both tables

INNER JOIN (Most Important)
SQL Query
SELECT students.name, courses.course
FROM students
INNER JOIN courses
ON students.id = courses.student_id;
Output
name	course
Akshay	CSE
Rahul	ECE
Step-by-Step Understanding
1. Take students table
2. Take courses table
3. Match rows where id = student_id
4. Combine data
Python Connection 🧠
students = [
 {"id":1,"name":"Akshay"},
 {"id":2,"name":"Rahul"}
]

courses = [
 {"student_id":1,"course":"CSE"},
 {"student_id":2,"course":"ECE"}
]

for s in students:
    for c in courses:
        if s["id"] == c["student_id"]:
            print(s["name"], c["course"])

👉 SQL JOIN = nested loops matching condition

Why INNER JOIN Works

👉 It only returns matching data from both tables

If no match → row is ignored ❌

Memory Trick 🧠
INNER JOIN = Only matching data
2️⃣ Types of JOINS (Overview)

Now let’s understand all types (very important for interviews)

1. INNER JOIN

👉 Only matching rows

✔ Most commonly used

2. LEFT JOIN

👉 All data from left table + matching from right

If no match → NULL

Example
SELECT *
FROM students
LEFT JOIN courses
ON students.id = courses.student_id;
Output
name	course
Akshay	CSE
Rahul	NULL

(if Rahul has no course)

3. RIGHT JOIN

👉 All data from right table + matching from left

4. FULL JOIN

👉 All data from both tables

Visual Understanding 🧠
INNER JOIN → common part only

LEFT JOIN → full left + match

RIGHT JOIN → full right + match

FULL JOIN → everything
Easy Memory Trick
LEFT JOIN → Left always stays
RIGHT JOIN → Right always stays
INNER JOIN → Only common stays
🔥 Placement Insight

Very common questions:

Q1: Difference between INNER JOIN and LEFT JOIN?
JOIN	Result
INNER JOIN	Only matching rows
LEFT JOIN	All left + matching right
Q2: What happens if no match in INNER JOIN?

👉 Row is removed

Q3: What happens if no match in LEFT JOIN?

👉 NULL is returned

Quick Revision (1 Minute)
JOIN = Combine tables

INNER JOIN → only matching
LEFT JOIN → left + match
RIGHT JOIN → right + match
FULL JOIN → all data
